MB = million  bytes
GB = billion  bytes
TP = trillion bytes

255 		    is the largest number 8  bit can represent (unsigned)
4.3 billion     is the largest number 32 bit can represent (unsigned)
9.2 quintallion is the largest number 64 bit can represent (with sighn, so in both direction +-)
1st bit is for sighn, 0 for positive and 1 for nagative.
